The paper deals with a dataset of Full HD videos and GPS data collected to capture the patterns of social and pedestrian behavior along traversed routes at different times. The purpose of the dataset is to make predictions about the risk associated with autonomously traveling along different routes. The paper applies Fast R-CNN pedestrian detection method to count the number of pedestrians at each video frame to assess the density of pedestrians along a route. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also deals with autonomous driving research, which falls under the category of Robotics (cs.RO). The paper also mentions the use of the dataset for long-term vision-based localization of mobile robots and autonomous vehicles, which falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also deals with the risk associated with autonomous driving, which falls under the category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR). Therefore, the likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR.
